4. Description of the operation of the Managing Board and the Supervisory Board and of the composition and operation of their committees

Siemens AG is subject to German corporate law. There fore, it has a twotier board structure, consisting of a Managing Board and a Supervisory Board. The duties and

Corporate Governance Statement

powers of the Managing Board and the Supervisory Board as well as the regulations regarding their operation and composition are defined primarily by the German Stock Corporation Act, the Articles of Association of Siemens AG and the bylaws for the Company’s governing bodies. The Articles of Association of Siemens AG, the Bylaws for the Managing Board, the Bylaws for the Supervisory Board and the bylaws for the Supervisory Board’s most important committees are available on the Siemens Global Website at WWW.SIEMENS.COM/ CORPORATE-GOVERNANCE.